  <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even">
    <div id="node-1167834" class="node node-teaser node-type-story"><div class="node-inner">



  

 <a href="/content/switching-monitor-profiles" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/11458f1.jpg" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/switching-monitor-profiles" title="Switching Monitor Profiles">Switching Monitor Profiles</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/kyle-rankin" title="View user profile.">Kyle Rankin</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Oct 24, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_207 first"><a href="/tag/desktop" rel="tag" title="">Desktop</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_23"><a href="/taxonomy/term/23" rel="tag" title="">Hardware</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_19"><a href="/tag/how-tos" rel="tag" title="">HOW-TOs</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_196 last active"><a href="/tag/tech-tips" rel="tag" title="" class="active">Tech Tips</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/switching-monitor-profiles" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
It's funny, when your home office is your couch, you tend to forget how
nice it can be when you dock a laptop and have all the extra screen real
estate a monitor brings. For many years, I left my work laptop docked
at work, and when I worked from home, I just VPNed in with a personal
laptop.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/switching-monitor-profiles"> more>></a></span></p>
  </div>



  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_comments first last"><a href="/content/switching-monitor-profiles#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">18 comments</a></li>
</ul>
 <!---->




</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->


  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-3 views-row-odd">
    <div id="node-1167436" class="node node-teaser node-type-story"><div class="node-inner">



  

 <a href="/content/non-linux-foss-launchy" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/11563fossf1.png" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/non-linux-foss-launchy" title="Non-Linux FOSS: Launchy!">Non-Linux FOSS: Launchy!</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/shawn-powers" title="View user profile.">Shawn Powers</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Oct 22, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_207 first"><a href="/tag/desktop" rel="tag" title="">Desktop</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_196 last active"><a href="/tag/tech-tips" rel="tag" title="" class="active">Tech Tips</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/non-linux-foss-launchy" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
With Unity's method for launching and finding programs and applications,
and OS X's spotlight tool becoming the new way to launch programs, the
entire way we think about launching programs is changing. Although I still
like to have a few icon shortcuts on my task bar, many folks prefer
a quick keystroke to bring up Gnome-Do, or Unity's launcher, or even
OS X's spotlight.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/non-linux-foss-launchy"> more>></a></span></p>
  </div>



  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_comments first last"><a href="/content/non-linux-foss-launchy#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">10 comments</a></li>
</ul>
