    <div id="node-1149050" class="node node-teaser node-type-story"><div class="node-inner">



  

 <a href="/content/non-linux-foss-notepad-better-better" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/11544fossf1_0.gif" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/non-linux-foss-notepad-better-better" title="Non-Linux FOSS: Notepad++ Is Better Better">Non-Linux FOSS: Notepad++ Is Better Better</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/shawn-powers" title="View user profile.">Shawn Powers</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Sep 17, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_369 first"><a href="/tag/foss" rel="tag" title="">FOSS</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_196 active"><a href="/tag/tech-tips" rel="tag" title="" class="active">Tech Tips</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_890"><a href="/tag/text-editor" rel="tag" title="">Text Editor</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_217 last"><a href="/tag/windows" rel="tag" title="">windows</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/non-linux-foss-notepad-better-better" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
If anyone understands the importance of a good text editor, it's a Linux
user stuck on Windows. Sure, Microsoft supplies Notepad and Wordpad,
but neither really feels like the powerful sort of text editor a Linux
user expects. Enter Notepad++.
<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/non-linux-foss-notepad-better-better"> more>></a></span></p>
  </div>



