 <a href="/content/sleep-android" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/11513sleepf1.jpg" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/sleep-android" title="Sleep as Android">Sleep as Android</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/shawn-powers" title="View user profile.">Shawn Powers</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Jul 04, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_192 first"><a href="/tag/android" rel="tag" title="">Android</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_29"><a href="/taxonomy/term/29" rel="tag" title="">Linux Journal</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_328"><a href="/tag/mobile" rel="tag" title="">Mobile</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_196 last active"><a href="/tag/tech-tips" rel="tag" title="" class="active">Tech Tips</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/sleep-android" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
I sleep poorly. In fact, insomnia has plagued me for years. As it turns
out, even when I think I'm sleeping well, I'm usually not. There's
nothing worse than a shoddy night's sleep followed by an abrupt alarm
going off when you've finally settled into a deep slumber.
</p>

<p>
Enter: Sleep as Android.
<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/sleep-android"> more>></a></span></p>
